description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about giving high quality nursing care with compassion?&lt;br /&gt;Do you have a desire to make a difference?&lt;br /&gt;Do you want to be supported to develop in your career?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for passionate and &quot;can do&quot; Band 3 Health Care Assistant on Ward 18&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for health care assistants with a genuine desire to look after cardiac and general medical patients. You should have a keen interest in providing high quality; harm free, patient centred care in a busy, fast paced, ever changing and often challenging environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this role you will need to demonstrate excellent communication skills, you must display a positive and professional manner, have a non- judgmental attitude, be open to change and have the drive and commitment to aim to get it right for every patient every time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your motivated and caring approach we will offer strong commitment to your personal and professional development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;f you are compassionate, and have strong and clear communication skills please contact us today and join one of the hardest working but friendliest teams in nursing!!&lt;br /&gt;Full time and part time vacancies are available. Flexibility is essential, internal rotation onto nights and possible rotation across the service in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: To be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameHelen SergeantJob titleWard MangerEmail addressHelen.Sergeant@lthtr.nhs.ukTelephone number01772523520&lt;/p&gt;
